      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA implementations (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) operate under documented software quality management systems. Version control, regression testing, and validation logs are maintained per institutional SOPs. Achieved level equals required level for this factor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions were exercised for each solver. Element formulation checks and patch tests confirm correct implementation of linear elastic constitutive behavior. No discrepancies identified beyond solver round-off tolerances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were conducted on the pedicle screw and rod assembly. Peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness quantities of interest changed by less than 2% between the medium and fine mesh densities, confirming adequate discretization for the intended QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Residual norms were monitored for all static analyses. Iterative solver convergence was confirmed with residual tolerances below 1e-6. Direct solver cross-checks were performed on a representative subset of load cases with agreement within 0.1%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Model setup procedures are documented in a controlled simulation plan reviewed by a second analyst. Boundary condition application, material property assignment, and contact definition were independently verified. No use errors identified during review."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive models are appropriate for the metallic titanium alloy components under quasi-static loading. Contact formulations capture screw-rod and rod-connector interactions. Model form assumptions are consistent with prior published literature on spinal implant FEA."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (elastic modulus, Poisson's ratio) sourced from certified material test reports for Ti-6Al-4V ELI. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of physical test specimens. Input uncertainty characterized through sensitivity analysis on key parameters."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested per ASTM F1717 protocol. Samples sourced from production lots with documented traceability. Sample dimensions measured and recorded; inter-specimen variability characterized and incorporated into model input distributions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load level and displacement rate per ASTM F1717 protocol. Only one test condition (compression-bending at standard offset) was evaluated. The absence of additional load configurations (e.g., torsion, fatigue) limits the breadth of validation coverage; this factor falls below the required level and represents a known gap in the validation activity."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs were matched to measured specimen geometry and material certificates. Fixture compliance was characterized experimentally and incorporated as boundary condition corrections. Agreement between nominal and as-measured inputs confirmed across all 11 specimens."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness and peak load at defined displacement from all three FEA implementations compared against experimental measurements. Mean absolute percentage error across N=11 specimens was below 8% for stiffness and below 10% for peak load. Statistical comparison using E2234 framework confirms acceptable agreement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak load under compression-bending are the primary quantities of interest for evaluating mechanical performance of pedicle screw systems. These QoIs are directly linked to clinical performance indicators and are the quantities reported in regulatory submissions for Class II spinal implant devices."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the ASTM F1717 compression-bending scenario directly. The test configuration, specimen geometry, and loading protocol are representative of the intended simulation use. Multi-laboratory participation (two independent test sites) increases confidence in the generalizability of validation findings."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for Model Risk Level 3. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) reflects the limitation of a single ASTM F1717 load configuration. The assessment team determined that this gap is acceptable given the well-characterized nature of the F1717 protocol, the multi-laboratory validation dataset, and the conservative nature of the compression-bending scenario relative to in vivo loading. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended regulatory decision for this Class II device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
